Density of ice: \( \rho_{i} = 0.917 \times 10^{3} \, \mathrm{kg/m}^{3} \);  
Latent heat of ice: \( L_{i} = 3.4 \times 10^{5} \, \mathrm{J/kg} \);  
Density of rock and magma: \( \rho_{r} = 2.9 \times 10^{3} \, \mathrm{kg/m}^{3} \);  
Specific heat capacity of rock and magma: \( c_{r} = 700 \, \mathrm{J/(kg \cdot {}^{\circ}\mathrm{C})} \);  
